Caridina flavilineata
Dang, 1975: 70-71, fig. 5. [Type locality: Nam Ha = Ha Nam and Nam Dinh Provinces, northern Vietnam]; 
Dang and Do (2008)
: 8-10, fig. 5; 
Dang and Ho (2012)
: 154-156, fig. 53.

Cephalothorax and cephalic appendages.
Carapace length 2.6-5.3 mm. Rostrum straight, reaching near to or slightly beyond end of antennular peduncle, 0.45-0.96 (median 0.6) times as long as carapace, rostral formula: 4-6+10-16/1-5 (n = 10), teeth normal (Fig. 
5
a
). Suborbital angle acute, completely fused with antennal spine; pterygostomian margin rounded (Fig. 
5
a
). Eyes well developed with globular cornea, anterior end reaching to 0.7 times length of basal segment of antennular peduncle (Fig. 
5
a
). Antennular peduncle 0.6-0.63 (median 0.61) times as long as carapace; basal segment 1.56-2.33 (median 2.0) times as long as second segment, second segment 1.2-1.67 (median 1.4) times as long as third segment (Fig. 
5
b
). Stylocerite reaching to 0.72 times length of basal segment of antennular peduncle (Fig. 
5
b
). Scaphocerite reaching beyond distal end of antennular peduncle, 3.0-4.33 (median 3.41) times as long as wide (Fig. 
5
c
).

This species inhabits mountain streams and rivers. We could not collect any specimens of this species from estuarine environments. In addition, based on egg-size (Table 
1
), we consider it as a land-locked species.
